      "id": "PopularPost235936",
      "post_content": "@Lamaron:  \nBoth effects are activated abilities that require a cost. You can't use one cost (in this case the saccing of a goblin) to activate multiple abilities.   \n  \nAnother piece to this is how a cost is paid. Payment of a cost occurs faster anything else and it can't be responded to. In your case, you would sacrifice Mogg Fanatic to it's own ability, pick who it's targeting (let's say to your opponent), and place \"Mogg Fanatic deals 1 damage to opponent\" onto the stack. Only after that ability is placed on the stack can you attempt to activate Goblin Sledder's ability, which is after Mogg Fanatic has been sent to the graveyard, meaning you can't activate Goblin Sledder using the already sacced Mogg.  \n  \nThe way you're thinking of it would be true if either of the abilities were triggered abilities. These 'trigger' when a specific something happens. For what you asked to happen, it would require one of the cards to say \"When a goblin is sacrificed, target creature gets +1/+1 until end of t... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "BastianQoU",
